ntic meaning or a recognizable Amharic root (Protocol 2).\n\n**Scholarly Guesses & Nuances:**\n- For 'ገርባ', while it can mean 'rough' or 'coarse' as an adjective, its frequent appearance with temporal or descriptive modifiers ('ባለፈው', 'አሁን', 'የትምህርት', 'የዓለም') suggests it is more likely functioning as a proper noun (a place name like Gerba) in these contexts. Both interpretations are included in the synonyms for completeness.\n- For 'ገሮችም', the root 'ገር' (gentle/meek) was chosen as the primary lemma, with 'ገረ' (a type of tree) noted as an alternative in the synonyms, as the context for disambiguation was absent. The 'ም' suffix indicates 'also' or 'even'.\n- All words underwent thorough morphological analysis to identify their true infinitive or base dictionary form, rather than simple prefix/suffix stripping. For instance, 'ገረፉአቸው' was lemmatized to 'መገረፍ' (to whip/flog), and 'ገርሞሻል' to 'መገረም' (to astonish/surprise).","input_words":["ገረፉአቸው","ገረፋቸው","ገሪማው","ገራዳ","ገራዳና","ገራፊዎችንና","ገርምት","ገርሞሻል","ገርባባለፈው","ገርባአሁን","ገርባየትምህርት","ገርባየዓለም","ገርቦ","ገርትለርና","ገርነቱንም","ገርጅፈው","ገርጥተውና","ገሮችም","ገሰረጆ","ገሰበ","ገሰጸኝ","ገሳበጥቂት","ገሳቢ","ገሳተባባሪ","ገሳግለሰቡ","ገበ","ገበሩለትም","ገበሩላቸውም","ገበሬዎቹንም","ገበብረ"],"batch_number":null,"batch_label":null,"model_version":"gemini-2.5-flash"},{"id":"10cf76b8-4523-4b69-a28a-9acc8abb7353","created_at":"2026-03-02T19:56:20.163674+00:00","word":null,"source_file":"rare_words_25/chunk_0587.txt","batch_index":0,"words":[{"pos":"Noun","root":"ድንጋጤ","word":"ድንጋጤያቸውን","synonyms":["panic","fear","shock","terror","dread"],"importance":8},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ድንግሊት","word":"ድንግሊት","synonyms":["virgin","maiden","pure woman"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ድንግልና","word":"ድንግልና","synonyms":["virginity","purity","chastity"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ድንግዥ","word":"ድንግዥ","synonyms":["twilight","dusk","gloaming"],"importance":6},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ድንጤ","word":"ድንጤ","synonyms":["gazelle","antelope","wild goat"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ድንጤ","word